    dc:creator "Shaw, Matthew D." ;
    dc:date "2014" ;
    dc:title "Ulyxes, a new Australopapuan mite genus associated with arboreal nests (Acari: Laelapidae)" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4948600>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4948608>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4948632>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4948644>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4948610>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4948614>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4948636>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4948598> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4948600>
    dc:description "FIGURES 6–9. Ulyxes calypso female ex Petaurus norfolcensis, Greenbank, QLD. 6, dorsum, scale = 100 µm; 7, venter, scale = 100 µm; 8, hypostomal area of gnathosoma, note fimbriae (f) on lateral arms of internal malae with expanded tips, and foliate trochanteral setae (pointers); 9, femur III, note apically bifid ad1, scale = 10 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4948600/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4948608>
    dc:description "FIGURES 16–21. Ulyxes euryclea female ex Glossy Black Cockatoo nest, Kangaroo Is, nest 245; 16, chelicerae, scale = 10 µm; 17, post-stigmatal plate showing gutter linking median (m) and posterior pore-like structures (only median visible in superficial SEM view) scale = 10 µm; 18, femur IV with apically bifid ad1 and ad2, scale = 10 µm; 19, habitus, ventral view, scale = 100 µm; 20, sclerotised plate-like structure at anterior pole of egg, rs = putative ramus sacculi, sf = putative sacculus foemineus, scale = 10 µm; 21, chelicera, anterior view showing apically divided tip, scale = 10 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4948608/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4948632>
    dc:description "FIGURES 38–42. Ulyxes penelope male, Boho, Victoria. 38, chelicera, scale = 50 µm; 39, gnathosoma, suture (s) marking top of tritosternal base, scale = 50 µm; 40, venter, scale = 100 µm; 41, femur II dorsal view, scale = 50 µm; 42, tibia and tarsus II ventral view, scale = 50 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4948632/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4948644>
    dc:description "FIGURES 52–57. Male chelicerae. 52, Ulyxes telemachus, Kioloa, NSW;53, U. penelope, Boho, Victoria; 54, U. ulixes Bauple SF, Queensland; 55, U. sisyphus, Timbillica; 56, U. euryclea; 57, U. laertes, Mt Clunie, NSW. All to same scale bar = 100 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4948644/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4948610>
    dc:description "FIGURES 22–24. Ulyxes euryclea males: 22, venter, ex Leadbeater’s possum, Yellingbo, nest 486, scale = 100 µm; 23, femur II, ventral view, scale = 50 µm; 24, chelicerae, arrow indicates triangular tip of spermatodactyl, ex Long-billed Corella, Templestowe, nest 87, scale = 50 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4948610/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4948614>
    dc:description "FIGURES 25–27. Ulyxes euryclea male ex Glossy Black Cockatoo nest, Kangaroo Island, nest 245: 25, ventral body, scale = 100 µm; 26, genital opening, scale = 10µm; 27, femur II, ventral view, scale = 10µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4948614/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4948636>
    dc:description "FIGURES 43–46. Ulyxes telemachus ex Antechinus stuartii, Kioloa, NSW. 43, female hypostomal area of gnathosoma, note broadened trochanteral setae (pointers), scale = 10 µm; 44, female habitus, dorsal view, note prominent gland pores (gd), scale = 100 µm; 45, female venter, scale = 100 µm; 46, male venter, scale = 100 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4948636/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4948598>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1–5. Ulyxes autolycus female. 1, dorsum, note gland pores (gd), holotype, scale = 100 µm; 2, gnathosoma, note fimbriae with inflated tips (f), labrum (la), paratype, scale = 50 µm; 3, chelicera, holotype, scale = 50 µm; 4, epistome, paratype, scale = 50 µm; 5, venter, holotype, suture (s) marking top of tritosternal base, exopodal IV shown on LHS only, scale = 100 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/4948598/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

